title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1980-05-12
lineage: Nak 700's > Sony TC158 Master Cassette, recorded front row balcony
description: Jack Straw-> Alabama Getaway-> El Paso, Althea, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication-> Far From Me, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider Feel Like A Stranger, Ship of Fools-> Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: front row balcony?? The lineage says "front row balcony". There is no balcony in the Boston Garden. It's a hockey arena....cm

What a Jam!! The second set of this show is absolutely phenomenal!  The post He's Gone jam is something you will want to hear, then want to play for your friends, then want to talk about with a Priest!  You will be thrilled, I promise!!

No Balcony?!?! Boston Garden most certainly did have a balcony, which overhung the lower-level seats by approximately ten rows.

Great tape by Mr. Rolfe, too!
hot stuff jerrys comes out on fire on this one and doesnt let up the hes gone jam is something worth a listen our plenty thats for sure overall id say the wholething is, sounds good for an Aud

Added to my I just finished streaming this entire show at work and it is HOT.  Decent AUD sound a s well.  2nd set energy is phenomenal.  Great version of Saint, crazy waltz-like jam after He's Gone, super high energy Sugar Mags and Jerry belting out the lyrics on US Blues.  A true gem.

Wish I was there...

Sound=4 stars, setlist=4 stars, performance=4.5 stars...4.17 overall.

Feel Like a Stringe-bag! Good AUD recording - love the way they mixed up the placment of feel like a stranger over this and the preceeding shows!

Does anyone know why this and some other AUD's are stream only?
Unreal If you can find something as good or better than this He's Gone> then turn it way way up and never lose it.

He's Gone... bernmclood, 

you might want to check out the He's Gone on the 1979-05-09 Broome County Arena show, it's one of the best i've heard yet. this is a fairly amazing version, but the '79 Broome county is by far my personal favorite.
Boston Garden Boston Garden had a balcony. The upper level hung out over the lower level by a few rows and ran all the way around the place.

Caution jam!!! Did anyone else notice the kinda distinct “Caution (do not stop on tracks)” jam in the post He’s Gone jam segment? I don’t see any reviewers mention it yet... but Phil starts and continues the Caution bass rifs and Jerry, followed by Bobby and even Brent for a second jump in on the power chords... just like in the old days.
